OL,3,CJersey cost of living higher than
OL,4,CLondon as recommended wage increases
OL,6,FThe Living Wage, which is calculated
OL,7,Faccording to the cost of household
OL,8,Fgoods and services, is higher in
OL,9,FJersey than in London.
OL,11,FCaritas Jersey, which sets the rate in
OL,12,Fthe island, has announced it will be
OL,13,F#15.10 per hour for 2026, a 7%
OL,14,Fincrease from this year and 2% higher
OL,15,Fthan London's Living Wage.
OL,17,FThe charity states it is the "minimum
OL,18,Fthat islanders need in order to thrive
OL,19,Fand not just survive", although it is
OL,20,Fa voluntary scheme that employers can
OL,21,Felect to sign up to.
