OL,3,CJersey cost of living higher than
OL,4,CLondon as recommended wage increases
OL,6,FThe Chief Executive Officer of Caritas
OL,7,FJersey, Patrick Lynch, adds: "The
OL,8,Fdifferential between the minimum wage
OL,9,Fand the Jersey Living Wage therefore
OL,10,Fremains worryingly high; something we
OL,11,Ffeel assembly members should ponder as
OL,12,Fthey debate the Budget this week and
OL,13,Flook ahead to next June's General
OL,14,FElection.
OL,16,F"The Jersey Living Wage has never been
OL,17,Fas important as it is now for so many
OL,18,Fpeople, with poverty unfortunately
OL,19,Fstill increasing and a continued rise
OL,20,Fin foodbank usage in our island."
